alt="Two elaborate chocolate milkshakes sitting on a messy table."
/>
</picture></div></div><div
class="block-intro-text"><p>A common theme in milkshake websites is to use bright color palettes to complement the business theme, or stark monochromatic color palettes to allow the milkshake photos to stand out. A milkshake business typically has a website if it offers franchising or catering, and includes information on the menu, allergies, contact details, and location.</p><p>Some nice-to-know information that a milkshake website may feature is whether the store has additional offerings, such as party venue hire for children, and whether the business operates through winter. Try our <a
href="/">milkshake AI website builder</a> to design your own site.</p></div><div
