class="entry-content"><div
class="entry-content-section"><h3 id="the-legendairy-milkshake-bar" class="entry-website-title">The Legendairy Milkshake Bar</h3><div
class="entry-website-img"><div
class="entry-faux-browser"><div
class="entry-browser-menu"><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div><div
class="dot"></div></div>
<picture>
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-legendairy-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=2:1,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=332&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 412px)" />
<source
data-srcset="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-legendairy-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=495&dpr=2" media="(max-width: 575px)" />
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-legendairy-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=650&dpr=2"
width="650"
height="403"
alt="desktop screenshot of website The Legendairy Milkshake Bar"
/>
</picture></div></div><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-url">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-link.svg" alt="chain icon" width="29" height="29" />
</span>
<a
class="force-single-line" href="https://www.legendairymilkshakebar.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">
https://www.legendairymilkshakebar.com/
</a></p><p
class="entry-website-detail website-detail-location">
<span
class="icon">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-pin.svg" alt="pin icon" width="30" height="30" />
</span>
<span>New Orleans, Louisiana, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>The Legendairy Milkshake Bar features over-the-top milkshakes topped with various desserts. The website has an interesting mix of contemporary and vintage styles that will draw customers in. The traditional top menu prioritizes information that customers will be most interested in, namely social media, locations, and the menu.</p><p>An interesting draw that is spotlighted in the top menu is the "gallon challenge," enticing customers through a sense of competition and the draw of winning a gift card.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>WAVE reports no errors on the site, indicating that the website has good accessibility. Contrast is good between the text, background, and images. The design of the site leans towards simplicity, focusing on images.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>There are too many different typefaces used on the site which can put off readers. The site is not completely compatible with assistive technologies and the main logo does not have enough contrast against the dark background.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-legendairy-20240522-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-legendairy-20240522-desktop.webp?crop=400:248,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=400&dpr=2"
alt="desktop screenshot of website"
width="400"
height="248"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The hero banner looks great on the desktop site, navigation is simple, and all necessary information is available. However, with the Instagram link being included in the menu bar, the bar runs a little long and runs over to the next line, which isn't as visually pleasing.</p><p>While the desktop site scores consistently highly in SEO, best practices, and accessibility, PageSpeed Insights notes slightly slower loading times, leading to an overall performance score of 66/100.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-legendairy-20240522-mobile.webp"
data-type="mobile"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
<img
class="lazyload"
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-legendairy-20240522-mobile.webp?crop=3:5,offset-x0,offset-y0&width=375&dpr=2"
alt="mobile screenshot of website"
width="325"
height="542"
/></div>
<img
class="lightbox-thumbnail-magnifier"
src="/assets/images/icon-magnifying.svg"
alt="magnifying glass"
width="50"
height="50"
/></div><div
class="entry-text"><p>The mobile site continues the theme of strong contrast between the brightly colored images and the black and white background, while the text remains a good size for the smaller screen. The menu, however, appears in a mint green block in white text, which lowers the contrast and makes reading difficult.</p><p>The menu is perhaps a bit too small and readers may need to enlarge the screen, but the navigation remains consistent across the desktop and mobile sites. The mobile site has a performance score of 26/100 on Google's PageSpeed Insights report.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div
