</span>
<span>Knoxville, Tennessee, U.S.</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>The Famous Milkshake Bar serves over-the-top, loaded milkshakes made with organic ingredients. The site is beautifully laid out, with quick access to the location, contact information, and social media links.</p><p>The top menu very simply lays out the drinks and dessert menu, contact details, and business information, but visitors to the site may be lacking additional information, including lists of allergens, online ordering options, and party reservation information.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>A clean and simple design aids with navigation while the drinks and dessert menu features colorful, enticing images and the option to click on a milkshake item to read a description of the ingredients.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is only semi-compliant with assistive technologies and WAVE reports a number of missing alternative text, empty links or headers, and contrast errors on the site. The logo on the desktop site is a bit too small in the menu.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-famous-milkshake-bar-20240528-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
