</span>
<span>Brampton, Ontario, Canada</span></p><div
class="entry-text"><p>Shake Therapy is a Canadian-based chain that offers a range of desserts, from milkshakes and Indian faloodas to waffles and cakes. Visitors to the site will enjoy the well-laid-out top menu and clear CTAs, but the milkshake menu is not in the top menu, necessitating customers to scroll to find it. However, potential customers will appreciate the inclusion of deals and a video.</p></div><h4>Pros and Cons</h4><div
class="entry-indented-box"><div
class="entry-website-pros">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-plus.svg" alt="plus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>WAVE reports a handful of missing alternative text and contrast errors, indicating a good page read. While colorful, the images and colors are not over-the-top or overwhelming in any way. PageSpeed Insights notes perfect SEO and best practices.</p></div></div><div
class="entry-website-cons">
<span
class="icon icon-sm">
<img
src="/assets/images/icon-minus.svg" alt="minus sign" width="18" height="18" />
</span><div
class="entry-text"><p>The site is not compliant with assistive technologies. The milkshake menu is not available in the top menu which seems like a bit of an oversight since this is a website dedicated specifically to milkshakes.</p></div></div></div><h4>Desktop Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-desktop"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-shake-therapy-20240528-desktop.webp"
data-type="desktop"
class="lightbox-trigger js-lightbox-trigger"
><div
class="lightbox-thumbnail">
